apps
Class ChangeDirectoryDummy

java.lang.Object
  apps.ChangeDirectoryDummy

public class ChangeDirectoryDummy
extends Object

Stand-in application for the change directory command.

The change directory command must manipulate the shell environment variables DFSHOST and DFSCWD, so it cannot be implemented in any Java program. The main purpose of this application is to be present in the list of applications that can be started by Launcher, and therefore to be shown in its usage message. The application can also be run to check that the cd command has received the appropriate number of arguments.

report

protected void report()
Reports that an argument has been processed successfully, for an application that processes multiple arguments.

The primary purpose of this method is to act as a checkpoint. Fatal errors are sometimes the result of code that is run in finally blocks. Such code typically avoids raising exceptions when it fails, in order to avoid masking a primary exception. Thus, fatal errors are signalled instead by calling the fatal method. A method which called fatal, but had no other errors, will appear to have returned successfully. report must be called after such a method is run to ensure that the fatal error causes termination of the program.

report

protected void report(apps.ApplicationFailure failure)
Reports that an argument has been processed, but the processing has caused a failure.

The failure is added to a list of application errors, and will be printed on application exit. If a fatal error has been signalled, the application exits immediately.
